Hi,

I have just put the sources of the Ocaml Link database into the repository at
camlcvs.inria.fr. They are located in the usercontrib/linkdb directory there.

If you want to participate in the development Xavier Leroy, as already
announced, will give you an ssh-based login. You need some software, but all is
free and usually part of Linux distributions:
	- ssh
	- cvs
	- Apache
and, of course, Ocaml (version 2.01).

Note that you can browse the repository even without login
(http://camlcvs.inria.fr). You'll find some initial documentation there.

I'm waiting for your ideas, please write me what you think the next goal could
be.

Gerd

